The reason why 0 is not counted as a first digit is that Java truncates any number that starts with 0 to the first non-zero place, and in your code, any seven digit number that starts with 0 would be truncated to the first non-zero digits place, which would be less than 7 digits long. For example, the number `00001` is parsed as `1`, as they both represent the same value. Anyways, consider using a `String` to store the number, as you can maintain the leading zeros and easily check for the correct length.
Also, consider using a true value for your do-while loop and break out of the loop when the correct value is entered.

    Scanner keyboard = new Scanner(System.in);
        do {
